<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-07-16T11:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-07-16T11:00:00-05:00" n="125" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d125">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">800.51W89 U.S.S.R./83a: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_BWC1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Bullitt</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-07-16T12:00:00-04:00">July 16,
                                    1934—noon</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>160. To be shown <persName corresp="#p_TAA1">Troyanovsky</persName>
                            please wire in briefest terms possible statement of substance of what
                            was understood in conversations with <persName corresp="#p_LMM1">Litvinov</persName> while here as to method of payment of
                            indebtedness by added interest on trade transactions supervised by
                            Export-Import Bank, and negativing suggestion that a straight cash loan
                            or a straight uncontrolled credit was ever contemplated. Think you were
                            present at all conversations and if so please make that clear. If you
                            think desirable send in nonconfidential code without making reference to
                            this telegram.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_HC1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>